    "title": "LESSON 40: THE '-OP-' SUFFIX",
    "header_color": "green",
    "pages": [
      {
        "page": 1,
        "total_pages": 1,
        "content": [
          "The suffix -OP- creates group adverbs from",
          "numbers. It means \"in a group of X.\"",
          "",
          "GROUPINGS:",
          "du      → duope       = two → in pairs",
          "tri     → triope      = three → in threes",
          "kvar    → kvarope     = four → in fours",
          "kvin    → kvinope     = five → in fives",
          "",
          "IN USE:",
          "Ni iris duope tra la parko.",
          "(We walked in pairs through the park.)",
          "",
          "COMPARE THE NUMBER SUFFIXES:",
          "-obl- = multiple (duobla = double)",
          "-on-  = fraction (duono = half)",
          "-op-  = group (duope = in pairs)",
          "-OP- tells you how many together!"
        ],
        "pronunciation": "Leciono kvardek"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
